The table objects are then parsed in accordance with the appropriate photovoltaic model in CDE-PV; for the DSC database, the PhotovoltaicCell model is used, and for the PSC database, the PerovskiteSolarCell model is used. This produces a number of chemical records, where each record describes a unique type of solar cell, and is populated by a number of sub-records that describe different properties of this type of solar cell. These sub-records can contain information about the cell metrology (e.g. active area), device characteristics (e.g. open-circuit voltage) and the material components (e.g. counter electrode). A full list of the supported datatypes is provided in Table 1.Table 1
