The second rows of Tables 6 and 7 show the results where the dye/perovskite was successfully extracted. The dye and perovskite have been emphasized since these act as the photoactive layer in the solar cell, a role that has one of the greatest effects on the cell efficiency. It is therefore crucial that these values are accurate. The third rows of these tables show cases where the dye/perovskite was successfully extracted alongside the four key photovoltaic properties, Voc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
